## Test Anti-Pattern Audit: `ProductCatalogTests.cs`

### Summary

| Severity | Count |
|----------|-------|
| **Critical** | 1 (systemic — affects 7 of 10 tests) |
| **High** | 0 |
| **Medium** | 1 |
| **Low** | 1 |

This is a textbook **coverage-touching** test class. Every public method on `ProductCatalog` is called, achieving line-coverage metrics, but almost nothing is actually verified. You have 95% coverage with near-zero confidence.

---

### 🔴 Critical: Coverage Touching / No Meaningful Assertions

**Pattern:** 7 of 10 tests either have *zero* assertions or only assert `IsNotNull` on a return type that can never be null (`List<T>`, `string`).

| Test Method | Problem |
|---|---|
| `AddProduct_Works` (L17) | No assertion at all — doesn't verify the product was stored. |
| `UpdatePrice_Works` (L33) | No assertion — never checks price actually changed. |
| `RemoveProduct_Works` (L39) | No assertion — never checks product was deleted. |
| `GetProductCount_Works` (L63) | No assertion — discards the count. |
| `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works` (L68) | No assertion — never checks prices were reduced. |
| `ImportFromCsv_Works` (L85) | No assertion — never checks product was imported. |
| `GetProduct_Works` (L25) | `Assert.IsNotNull` only — doesn't verify Name, Price, or Sku match. |
| `SearchProducts_Works` (L46) | `Assert.IsNotNull` only — doesn't verify result count or content. |
| `GetAllProducts_Works` (L55) | `Assert.IsNotNull` only — doesn't verify the list has items. |
| `ExportToCsv_Works` (L77) | `Assert.IsNotNull` only — doesn't verify CSV content. |

**Why it's Critical:** These tests will pass even if every method silently does nothing. Bugs in `UpdatePrice`, `ApplyBulkDiscount`, or `ImportFromCsv` (e.g., wrong discount math, CSV parsing errors on multi-line input) slip straight to production.

**Fix — representative examples:**

```csharp
// Before (L33-36)
[TestMethod]
public void UpdatePrice_Works()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
    _catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);
}

// After
[TestMethod]
public void UpdatePrice_UpdatesStoredPrice()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
    _catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);
    var updated = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
    Assert.AreEqual(14.99m, updated!.Price);
}
```

